request.description:
# Fetch Title Info

This API endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to get information about a title.

## Request

The request should be sent to `localhost:9876/ntuaflix_api/info/title/:titleID`

### Path Parameters

- `titleID` (string, required): The unique identifier for the title.
    

```
GET localhost:9876/ntuaflix_api/info/title/:titleID

 ```

### Query Parameters

- format(string, optional): The response format. It can have one of the values "json" or "csv".
    

## Response

Upon a successful execution, the API returns a status code of 200 and a JSON object with the following structure:

``` json
{
    "titleID": "",
    "type": "",
    "originalTitle": "",
    "titlePoster": "",
    "startYear": "",
    "endYear": "",
    "genres": [
      {
        "genreTitle": ""
      }
    ],
    "titleAkas": [
      {
        "akaTitle": "",
        "regionAbbrev": ""
      }
    ],
    "principals": [
      {
        "nameID": "",
        "name": "",
        "category": ""
      }
    ],
    "rating": {
      "avRating": "",
      "nVotes": ""
    }
}

 ```

The response provides detailed information about the title, including its ID, type, original title, poster, start and end year, genres, alternate titles, principals, and rating. It is also possible to receive the response in csv format by using the format query parameter.

- `minrating` : The minimum rating for the titles to be included.

{

  "minrating": ""

## Search Name

This API endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to search for a specific name in the ntuaflix database based on a part provided in the request body.

### Request

- Method: GET
- Endpoint: `localhost:9876/ntuaflix_api/info/searchname`
- Request Body (raw, JSON):
    
    ``` json
              {
                "namePart": ""
              }
    
     ```
    

### Query Parameters

- format(string, optional): The response format. It can have one of the values "json" or "csv".
    

### Response

- Status: 200 OK
- Content-Type: application/json or text/csv based on the format query parameter
- Body:
    
    ``` json
              [
                {
                  "nameID": "",
                  "name": "",
                  "namePoster": "",
                  "birthYr": "",
                  "deathYr": "",
                  "profession": "",
                  "nameTitles": [
                    {
                      "titleID": "",
                      "category": ""
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
    
     ```
    

This endpoint returns a JSON array containing information related to the searched name, including nameID, name, namePoster, birthYr, deathYr, profession, and nameTitles with titleID and category.
